The paper proposes a method for predicting motion of tracked agents in interactive environments, which is a problem commonly studied in robotics (cs.RO). The method involves using a model of the environment to aid in motion prediction, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the proposed approach using a benchmark pedestrian tracking problem and a robot arm manipulation task, which are tasks commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
